TextBody:
Hello Jakob,

 Thank you for contact Netwrix Support.  Currently, it is not possible to manage your organizations users on the Netwrix Customer Portal.  When a person registers to use our Customer portal they are associated with the account of the same domain as the user's email address. Similarly, licenses are displayed in the Customer Portal based on that account association.

I will pass your request to be able to manage your organization's access to the customer portal to be considered as a future enhancement.

Please let us know if there is anything else we can assist with?

Thank you,

Brandon West
Technical Support Manager
Phone: 1-949-407-5125 | Toll-free: 888-638-9749
____________________ __________
Powerful Data Security Made Easy

6160 warren Parkway, Suite 100, Frisco, TX 75034
www.netwrix.com
ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0N32jD:ref
Subject: Access to the netwrix portal    [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0N32jD:ref ]

ref:_00D7091pB._500Q000N32jD:ref

Okay, so basically you are saying any employee with the same domain prefix, in this case @aevengroup.com, will, after they are created on the customer portal, have access to ALL the licensing purchase under this domain?

What is we, the company, do not want just anybody with a company domain email address to have access to ALL licensing/software purchase by netwrix?
Subject: Netwrix Support Ticket #439103 - Access to the netwrix portal
